div.p:
Concerned by the threat to peace and freedom
presented by the aggression in Korea and the danger of aggression
elsewhere;

Reaffirms its res 290 (IV) entitled Essentials of
Peace, regrets that certain members states have failed to Comply with
said res and calls upon all members of the UN to carry out that res;

list.item:
To put an end to aggression and subversion and to the betrayal
                                    of nationalist independence movements in the interest of a new
                                    imperialism;

For the regulation and reduction of all armaments and mass
                                    armies by means of effective systems of control and
                                    inspection;

For a free world dedicated to the observance of human rights,
                                    to the removal of barriers to friendly intercourse among
                                    peoples, and to the free communication of ideas;
